risk elements  the following table presents the amounts of non-performing loans and card member receivables that are either non-accrual, past due, or restructured, segregated between u.s. and non-u.s. borrowers.
past due loans are loans that are contractually past due 90 days or more as to principal or interest payments. restructured loans and card member receivables are those that meet the definition of a tdr.
